  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Iasi railway station was full of thousands of people trying to hang on the trains heading to Bucharest, and we were one of the few lucky ones who managed to get into the train under the escort of the Romanian Army, through the bribery to one of their officers.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were put, the whole family, Fliss family, in this tiny little compartment for eight people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Probably, we were like 20.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from the outside, there were the Iron Guards shouting and screaming.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a decision was made that none of us should show their faces at the window because they may be taken as Jews, and the Iron Guard would throw us out from the train, with my exception.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They decided that I don't look Jewish, and actually, I should stand in front of this window to show the Iron Guards on the platform that it was a Christian compartment.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the end of the coach, we saw a terrible scene when my teacher, my school teacher, who was red-haired, a man in his 30s or 40s, was dragged by the Iron Guards and thrown away with shoutings of 'Yid' and beaten up and left on the floor of the platform.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was actually lucky because they could have been waiting for the train to run and throw him from the running train.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The trip took about three days, but we were equipped with food, boiled eggs and bread and water, so we reached Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were many stops and stations and the lines, which were letting military trains with troops to go, and trains with wounded soldiers and mobile hospitals and you name it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The train was full, including the roof of the train was full of passengers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we reached Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
